==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
* Of Hebrew origin [[יהושׁוּע]] (alternate spelling: [[יהושׁע]]) {{HH|3091}}

===Pronunciation===
*Ἰησοῦς / Iēsous / ee-ay-sooce'

===Proper Noun===
'''Ἰησοῦς'''

# [[Jesus]] (that is, Jehoshua, Joshua), the name of the founder of [[Christianity]] and four other Israelites: - [[Jesus]].

